### GPS Tracking API Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:5270

### Step 1: Register a driver account
POST http://localhost:5270/api/auth/register-driver
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "driver1@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123!",
  "displayName": "John Driver"
}

### Step 2: Login to get JWT token
POST http://localhost:5270/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "driver1@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123!"
}

@authToken = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Step 3: Post a GPS breadcrumb (driver location)
POST http://localhost:5270/api/gps/breadcrumb
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @authToken

{
  "latitude": 40.7128,
  "longitude": -74.0060,
  "speed": 25.5,
  "heading": 180.0,
  "accuracy": 5.0,
  "deviceTimestamp": "2026-04-07T10:30:00Z",
  "tripId": null
}

### Step 4: Post another GPS breadcrumb with a trip
POST http://localhost:5270/api/gps/breadcrumb
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer @authToken

{
  "latitude": 40.7150,
  "longitude": -74.0080,
  "speed": 30.0,
  "heading": 180.0,
  "accuracy": 4.5,
  "deviceTimestamp": "2026-04-07T10:35:00Z",
  "tripId": 1
}

### Step 5: Get trip breadcrumbs (GPS history for a specific trip)
GET http://localhost:5270/api/gps/trip/1/breadcrumbs
Authorization: Bearer @authToken

### Step 6: Get driver's latest position (for driver ID 1)
GET http://localhost:5270/api/gps/driver/1/latest
Authorization: Bearer @authToken

### Step 7: Get all active drivers' positions
GET http://localhost:5270/api/gps/drivers/active
Authorization: Bearer @authToken

### Step 8: Get all active drivers' positions (with custom time threshold of 60 minutes)
GET http://localhost:5270/api/gps/drivers/active?minutesThreshold=60
Authorization: Bearer @authToken

### SignalR WebSocket Testing
### Connect to: ws://localhost:5270/gps-hub?access_token=YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### After connecting to WebSocket, send this message to broadcast driver location:
### {"type": 1, "target": "BroadcastDriverLocation", "arguments": [{ "driverId": 1, "driverName": "John Driver", "latitude": 40.7128, "longitude": -74.0060, "speed": 25.5, "heading": 180.0, "tripId": null, "timestamp": "2026-04-07T10:30:00Z" }]}

### Subscribe to specific driver updates:
### {"type": 1, "target": "SubscribeToDriver", "arguments": [1]}

### Receive driver location updates (server sends):
### {"type": 1, "target": "DriverLocationUpdated", "arguments": [{ "driverId": 1, "driverName": "John Driver", "latitude": 40.7128, "longitude": -74.0060, "speed": 25.5, "heading": 180.0, "tripId": null, "timestamp": "2026-04-07T10:30:00Z" }]}
